<TITLE> Rubber growers seek protection, facilities </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)The rubber growers have pleaded with the government to help protect the rubber industry from the importers. A ninemember delegation of Bangladesh Rubber Garden Owners Association met the state minister for forest and environment Mostafizar Rahman Fizar at the Secretariat on Wednesday. Mostafizar promised steps. The association leaders informed the minister that out of the total 1300 rubber gardens in the country, the owners of 350 gardens owed the government Tk 16 crore. The government closed the gardens and operations of the industries which put the owners and employees into much trouble, the leaders said The rubber association leaders demanded imposition of tariff and other barriers on rubber import and introduction of incentive for the rubber industries like readymade garment industries. The association president Abu Sayeed and secretary general HM Harunur Rashid led the delegation to the meeting
